      "@context": "http://www.w3.org/ns/anno.jsonld",
      "type": "Annotation",
      "body": [
        {
          "type": "TextualBody",
          "purpose": "transcribing",
          "value": "I know that the tide is not an independent force, but merely the submission of the water to the\nmovement of the moon in its orbit. And this orbit in its turn is subject to other orbits which are\nmightier far than it. And so the whole universe is held fast in the clinging grip of strong hands,\nthe forces of Earth and Sun, planets, and comets, and galaxies, blindly erupting forces ceaselessly\nstirring in ripples of silence to the very depth of black space. Amos Oz",
          "language": "en"
        }
      ],
